		<msContents>
			<summary><bibl><ptr target="bib:ARIE1943-1945"/></bibl> (p. 40): <quote>In characters of about the 9th century A.D. Beginning and ends of lines built in. Seems to state that the temple of Vaikuṇṭanāthar was constructed by a Brāhmaṇa lady named Kumariccāṉi.</quote> <bibl><ptr target="bib:Nagaswamy1970_02"/></bibl> (p. 28): <quote>An inscription in the 8-9th century Tamil characters recording 
				the construction of a Viṣṇu temple called Śrī kōil Śrī Vaikuṇṭatēvar by a
				Brahmin lady Kumāriccāṇi, the wife of a certain Dharman, is found on
				a slab built into the ceiling of the <foreign>ardhamaṇḍapa</foreign> of Kariyamāṇikka
				Vaikuṇṭa Varadarājar temple.</quote></summary>
		</msContents>
